\cf1
{What are the guidelines for conducting effective meetings?}\plain \f0
\fs2
\cf1
{\par
}\plain \f0
\fs2
\cf1
\pard
\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0
\li0\ri0\fi0
\ql\sa1\plain \f0
\fs22
\cf1
{\par
}\plain \f0
\fs22
\cf1
\pard
\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0
\li0\ri0\fi0
\ql\tx0\tx634\tx1958\tx2592\tx3916\tx4550\tx5874\tx6508
{ANS:\tab }\plain \f0
\fs22
\cf1
{\par
}\plain \f0
\fs22
\cf1
\pard
\widctlpar\keep\hyphpar0
\li0\ri0\fi0
\ql\plain \f1
\fs22
\cf1
{\'95
Define the purpose and intended outcome of the meeting. Be specific about what 
should happen as a result of the meeting. Is the purpose to brainstorm ideas, pro
vide status information, or solve a problem? Make the purpose of a meeting very c
lear to all meeting planners and participants.\par
}\plain \f1
\fs22
\cf1
{\par
}\plain \f1
\fs22
\cf1
{\'95
Determine who should attend the meeting. Many meetings are most effective with 
the minimum number of participants possible, especially if decisions must be made
.\par
}\plain \f1
\fs22
\cf1
{\par
}\plain \f1
\fs22
\cf1
{\'95
Provide an agenda to participants before the meeting. Meetings are most effecti
ve when the participants come prepared.\par
}\plain \f1
\fs22
\cf1
{\par
}\plain \f1
\fs22
\cf1
{\'95
Prepare handouts and visual aids, and make logistical arrangements ahead of tim
e. By creating handouts and visual aids, you must organize thoughts and ideas. Th
is usually helps the entire meeting run more effectively.\par
}\plain \f1
\fs22
\cf1
{\par
}\plain \f1
\fs22
\cf1
{\'95
Run the meeting professionally. Introduce people, restate the purpose of the me
eting, and state any ground rules that attendees should follow.\par
}\plain \f1
\fs22
\cf1
{\par
}\plain \f1
\fs22
\cf1
{\'95
Set the ground rules for the meeting. State up front how the meeting will be ru
n.\par
}\plain \f1
\fs22
\cf1
{\par
}\plain \f1
\fs22
\cf1
{\'95
Build relationships. Depending on the culture of the organization and project, 
it may help to build relationships by making meetings fun experiences.}\plain \f0
